<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="561" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-06-13"><hi rend="italic">June 13,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Provisional Government succeeded Ezeta’s administration. Actual President
                            is Gen. Rafael Gutierrez. He demands surrender Salvadoreans on board <hi rend="italic">Bennington</hi>. Consul Pollock at Acajutlas on
                            business.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>